The paper proposes a modification to the Model-Agnostic Meta-Learning (MAML) framework, which is a popular approach in machine learning for few-shot learning tasks. The proposed modification involves identifying the mode of tasks sampled from a multimodal task distribution and adapting quickly through gradient updates. The paper evaluates the proposed model on a diverse set of few-shot learning tasks, including regression, image classification, and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.RO (Robotics).
